com.bigdata.bop

Interface IConstraint

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BOp, Cloneable, IPropertySet, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IValueExpressionConstraint<X>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Constraint, ProjectedConstraint, SPARQLConstraint, TryBeforeMaterializationConstraint

    public interface IConstraint
extends BOp, Serializable
    An interface for specifying constraints on the allowable states of an IBindingSet. For example, you can impose the constraint that two variables must have distinct bindings the constraint that a binding must be (or must not be) a particular value type, or that the binding must take on one of a set of enumerated values.
